τ-Rec benchmark data license
=============================

The benchmark task definitions in `tasks/`, the movie catalog `catalog.json`,
the policy document `policy.md`, the answer key `answers.json`, and the
task baseline `task_baseline.json` are released under the Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0).

You are free to:
  - Share — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format
  - Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the material for any purpose,
    even commercially.

Under the following terms:
  - Attribution — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the
    license, and indicate if changes were made. You may do so in any reasonable
    manner, but not in any way that suggests the licensor endorses you or
    your use.

Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

Source attribution
------------------

The movie catalog (`catalog.json`) is derived from data sourced via
The Movie Database (TMDB) public REST API. Per TMDB's terms of use, this
product uses the TMDB API but is not endorsed or certified by TMDB.

When citing the benchmark data, please cite:

  Narasimhan, B. S. and Narasimhan, K. R. (2026).
  τ-Rec: A Verifiable Benchmark for Agentic Recommender Systems.
  In Proceedings of the 20th ACM Conference on Recommender Systems (RecSys '26).
